      {
        "title": "UserRecon",
        "content": "# How to Install and Run the UserRecon Tool\n\n**Last Updated:** 23 July 2025\n\nUserRecon is an OSINT (Open-Source Intelligence) tool used to search for a username across 75+ social media platforms. It helps investigators determine whether a specific username exists on multiple websites such as:\n\n* Twitter (X)\n* Instagram\n* YouTube\n* Reddit\n* WordPress\n* GitHub\n* MySpace\n* And many others\n\nThis tool is useful for digital investigations, cybersecurity research, and brand monitoring.\n\n> ⚠️ Use this tool responsibly and only for lawful, ethical investigations.\n\n---\n\n# 🔧 Installation Guide\n\n### Step 1: Clone the Repository\n\nOpen your terminal and run:\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/issamelferkh/userrecon\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Change Directory\n\nNavigate into the cloned folder:\n\n```bash\ncd userrecon\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: List Files (Optional)\n\nTo view all files, including hidden ones:\n\n```bash\nls -la\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 4: Make Script Executable\n\nChange permissions of the script:\n\n```bash\nchmod +x userrecon.sh\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 5: Run the Tool\n\nExecute the script:\n\n```bash\n./userrecon.sh\n```\n\nThe tool will start and display the main interface.\n\n---\n\n# 🚀 How to Use UserRecon\n\n1. After launching the tool, you will be prompted to enter a username.\n2. Type the username you want to search.\n3. Press Enter.\n4. The tool will scan across supported social media platforms.\n5. If the username exists, it will return the profile links.\n\n\n![cheatsheet](https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20210702210823/1.png)\n\n---\n\n# 📁 Output File\n\nAfter completion, the results are saved automatically in a file named:\n\n```\n<username>.txt\n```\n\nExample:\nIf you searched for the username **Talha**, the results will be saved in:\n\n```\nTalha.txt\n```\n\n---\n\n# 📖 Viewing the Results\n\nTo open the file using the `vi` editor:\n\n```bash\nvi Talha.txt\n```\n\nTo exit `vi` without saving changes:\n\n```\nShift + ZQ\n```\n\nYou may also open the file with:\n\n```bash\ncat Talha.txt\n```\n\nor\n\n```bash\nnano Talha.txt\n```\n\n---\n\n# 🧠 Why Use UserRecon?\n\n* Saves time when checking username availability\n* Useful in OSINT investigations\n* Helps in digital footprint analysis\n* Assists in brand protection research\n* Helpful in cybersecurity assessments\n\n---\n\n# ⚖️ Ethical Use Reminder\n\nUserRecon should only be used for:\n\n* Open-source intelligence research\n* Cybersecurity investigations\n* Personal username checks\n* Brand monitoring\n\nDo not use it for harassment, stalking, or violating privacy.\n\n---\n"
      }
