        "title": "Zphisher",
        "content": "\n## **Zphisher – Automated Phishing Tool**\n\n---\n\n### **Description**\nZphisher is a powerful, open-source phishing tool designed for Kali Linux. It simplifies phishing attacks by providing ready-made templates for popular websites. It is considered easier to use than the Social Engineering Toolkit (SET). Zphisher allows attackers to create phishing pages and capture credentials (IDs and passwords) over a Wide Area Network (WAN).\n\n---\n\n### **Key Features**\n- 100% open-source\n- Written in Bash\n- Lightweight – minimal storage usage\n- Simple and easy-to-use interface\n- 33+ phishing page templates\n- Custom template support\n- Works over WAN (not limited to LAN)\n- Real-time credential capture displayed in terminal\n\n---\n\n### **Supported Platforms (Templates)**\nZphisher includes templates for:\n- Facebook  \n- Instagram  \n- Google  \n- Snapchat  \n- GitHub  \n- Yahoo  \n- Proton Mail  \n- Spotify  \n- Netflix  \n- LinkedIn  \n- WordPress  \n- Origin  \n- Steam  \n- Microsoft  \n*(and others)*\n\n---\n\n### **Installation & Setup**\n```bash\ncd Desktop\ngit clone git://github.com/htr-tech/zphisher.git\ncd zphisher\nbash zphisher.sh\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Usage Workflow**\n1. Run the tool: `bash zphisher.sh`\n2. Select a platform from the numbered list (e.g., `2` for Instagram)\n3. Choose a phishing template style (e.g., `1` for Default)\n4. A phishing URL is generated\n5. Send the link to the target\n6. Credentials entered by the victim are captured and displayed in the terminal\n\n---\n\n### **Example Use Case (Instagram Phishing)**\n- Option selected: `2` (Instagram)\n- Template: `1` (Default)\n- Generated link: `ezlikers` (example)\n- Victim enters ID and password\n- Credentials appear instantly in the attacker’s terminal\n\n---\n\n### **Important Note**\nThis tool is intended **for educational and authorized security testing only**. Unauthorized use for phishing or credential theft is illegal and unethical.\n\n--- \n ![cheatsheet](https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20210515165619/18.PNG)"
